timelineItems.name: JP Stats
timelineItems.text: .@WhitecapsFC Kendall Waston is one of only 4 field players that have played ALL of its club's minutes this season. #NYvVAN

timelineItems.desc: Sacha Kljestan (New York Red Bulls) is shown an early red card for an elbow on Kendall Waston (Vancouver Whitecaps).
timelineItems.title: RED CARD: Sacha Kljestan given a straight red

timelineItems.name: Farhan Devji
timelineItems.text: That's Ousted's first-ever PK save out of nine attempts. Huge. Kekuta looks lively again, too. #VWFC #NYvVAN

timelineItems.name: Dan Dickinson
timelineItems.text: Red card to Sacha Kljestan. This is off the rails quick. #NYvVAN

timelineItems.name: CommutingOTP
timelineItems.text: Red bull Arena #NYvVAN http://t.co/YWQC0rM5AJ

timelineItems.name: Vancouver Whitecaps
timelineItems.text: Red card to #NYRB!

timelineItems.name: Jason Baum
timelineItems.text: Red card to Sacha Kljestan in the 10th minute. #NYvVAN

timelineItems.name: Larry Wong
timelineItems.text: Waston down, and New York is now reduced to ten men. #VWFC

timelineItems.name: John Corbett
timelineItems.text: Shots fired by 'Caps contingent. #RBNY against modern football? Only if 'modern' means artificial turf. #NYvVAN http://t.co/CQIXwkD51s

timelineItems.name: Vancouver Whitecaps
timelineItems.text: Kickoff just 10 minutes away. News and notes on #VWFC's starting lineup: http://t.co/67GmvcqBBO #NYvVAN http://t.co/bGKkBwxcQR

timelineItems.name: Frank Giase
timelineItems.text: And the game turns that quickly. Wright-Phillips misses a PK and then Kljestan gets a red card. #NYvVAN #MLS #RBNY

timelineItems.name: Ben Hickey
timelineItems.text: KLJESTAN'S OFF! A 'coming together' between him and Waston who goes down like he's been shot. What a start to this game! #NYvVAN

timelineItems.name: Haig
timelineItems.text: The series of comedy pratfalls from Waston aside, Kljestan ought to know better than to poke at an opponent like that. #NYvVAN

timelineItems.name: Chris Hoenig
timelineItems.text: Disastrous opening 10 mins for #RBNY. Forget the ref, this team needs to get their heads in the game. #VWFC is in their heads.

timelineItems.desc: Goal! New York Red Bulls 0, Vancouver Whitecaps FC 1.  Kekuta Manneh (Vancouver Whitecaps FC) puts home a nice cross by Steven Beitashour.
timelineItems.title: GOAL: Kekuta Manneh makes it 1-0

timelineItems.name: Eric Giacometti
timelineItems.text: Goal #VWFC! Manneh taps in from close range after a beautifully whipped in cross. #RBNY down 1-0. #NYvVAN

timelineItems.name: Jarred
timelineItems.text: Manneh! 1-0 #WhitecapsFC! What a goal! #VWFC

timelineItems.name: Russ McKenzie
timelineItems.text: Welp - #VWFC puts the call in the net first. Manneh made it look easy. #NYvVAN

timelineItems.name: Russ McKenzie
timelineItems.text: Unfortunately for #RBNY, this match had the wheels fall off right quick - missed PK, Sacha red card, now #VWFC early goal #NYvVAN

timelineItems.name: Andy Edwards
timelineItems.text: Earth to Chris Duvall… Earth to Chris Duvall… Are you out there? Can you hear us? If so, Kekuta Manneh is your man on that play. #NYvVAN

timelineItems.desc: Long range shot by Octavio Rivero (Vancouver Whitecaps) nails the woodwork.
timelineItems.title: CHANCE: Octavio Rivero stings the post

timelineItems.name: Dan Dickinson
timelineItems.text: Marsch had talked earlier in the week about needing their best performance of the year against Vancouver. Safe to say this isn't it. #NYvVAN

timelineItems.name: Larry Wong
timelineItems.text: Great pass by Beitashour to Manneh and now I know why Manneh is called Scooter. #VWFC #BeepBeep CC: @kekuta16, @WhitecapsFC

timelineItems.name: Dan Dickinson
timelineItems.text: OFF THE POST! Rivero dribbles downfield. Has options, takes the shot himself, and it pings off the woodwork. #NYvVAN

timelineItems.name: The View From 102
timelineItems.text: Robles beaten like a rented mule, saved by the post - this is getting ugly #RBNY #NYvVAN

timelineItems.desc: The New York Red Bulls and Vancouver Whitecaps meet for the only time in league play this season when the clubs face off Saturday evening at Red Bull Arena.
timelineItems.title: HIGHLIGHTS: New York Red Bulls vs Vancouver Whitecaps FC | June 20, 2015

timelineItems.desc: David Ousted denies Bradley Wright-Phillips on two different penalty kicks in the same game.
timelineItems.title: TWO PK SAVES in one game by David Ousted

timelineItems.name: New York Red Bulls
timelineItems.text: 20: Felipe nicely chips a FK into the top corner, but David Ousted is there for the stop. 0-1 #NYvVAN

timelineItems.name: Michael Vazquez
timelineItems.text: Kljestan lost his head. That should be more than just 1 game. #RBNY #NYvVAN

timelineItems.name: Dan Dickinson
timelineItems.text: Players are out of the tunnel under weirdly grey skies. #NYvVAN

timelineItems.name: Steven Lamothe
timelineItems.text: We win by 8 and we're top of the table again. Cmon #VWFC

timelineItems.name: Edward Soliman
timelineItems.text: I picked the right week to skip the #NYvVAN game. #RBNY turning into a #CharlieFoxtrot.

timelineItems.name: Daniel Bettridge
timelineItems.text: Rivero looks good tonight. His hold up play is all too often under appreciated #VWFC

timelineItems.name: Matthew Doyle
timelineItems.text: I counted a 16-pass build-up for @WhitecapsFC on the Manneh goal. Pulled RBNY apart & Duvall caught napping. #NYvVAN

timelineItems.name: Eighty Six Forever
timelineItems.text: That shot by Rivero almost snuck in there out of nothing. I went "Oh come on......OMG!" #NYvVAN #VWFC

timelineItems.name: New York Red Bulls
timelineItems.text: 25: Sal Zizzo chases down the ball for a cross, but falls out of bounds as he gets off the shot. 0-1 #NYvVAN

timelineItems.name: Larry Wong
timelineItems.text: The half so far: Ousted saved a PK, New York reduced to 10 men, and Manneh scores. #VWFC

timelineItems.name: Russ McKenzie
timelineItems.text: Mike Grella's got moves like Jagger #RBNY #NYvVAN

timelineItems.name: New York Red Bulls
timelineItems.text: 27: Mike Grella earns a corner for the Red Bulls. 0-1 #NYvVAN

timelineItems.name: New York Red Bulls
timelineItems.text: Ready? Ready! #NYvVAN! #RBNY http://t.co/DI8X2s7KOU

timelineItems.name: ToeKneeNo  M.
timelineItems.text: @NewYorkRedBulls BWP starting to look like a frustrated Henry last 4 or 5 games. And THAT'S not a good thing. #RBNY @EmpireOfSoccer #NYvVAN

timelineItems.name: Vancouver Whitecaps
timelineItems.text: 29' 1-0 The game has settled down after that crazy start. 'Caps are enjoying all the extra space out there. #VWFC

timelineItems.name: Vancouver Whitecaps
timelineItems.text: Beitashour to Manneh to the back of the net. Watch the great goal to make it 1-0 #VWFC https://t.co/cDsLYWvmlT

timelineItems.name: Jason Kurylo
timelineItems.text: Really, TSN? You put #TFC on the main channel, but the #NYvVAN #WhitecapsFC match gets knocked to TSN2 by fricking golf? Dinks.

timelineItems.name: New York Red Bulls
timelineItems.text: 36: Chris Duvall sends in a good cross, it's cleared by Vancouver, but picks up a corner for the Red Bulls. 0-1 #NYvVAN

timelineItems.desc: Penalty saved! David Ousted (Vancouver Whitecaps) dives to his right to save the PK by Bradley Wright-Phillips (New York Red Bulls).
timelineItems.title: PK SAVE: David Ousted denies Bradley Wright-Phillips

timelineItems.name: bill gordon
timelineItems.text: Being a #RBNY supporter is a form of punishment. Got offered free #NYvVAN tickets & passed because of the weather but truthfully they stink.

timelineItems.name: Christian Araos
timelineItems.text: Credit to #RBNY for remaining compact & organized in defense w/ 10 men. Most of #VWFC's chances have come from individual efforts. #NYvVAN

timelineItems.name: Christian B
timelineItems.text: I come home and so much had happened this half? Ousted PK save and NYRB down to 10 men? #noice #VWFC

timelineItems.name: Frank Giase
timelineItems.text: Felipe has to go forward to have any offense, but @WhitecapsFC are taking advantage of space behind him. #NYvVAN #RBNY #MLS

timelineItems.name: bill gordon
timelineItems.text: Sacha Kljestan sent off via red card. Terrible signing by the #RBNY. Firing @petkemike looks worse & worse. Embarrassing. #NYvVAN

timelineItems.name: Juan Escalante
timelineItems.text: Shep's chastising the South Ward for not "lifting" the team. The relationship goes two ways, Shep. The team's gotta earn it. #NYvVAN

timelineItems.desc: Shot by Octavio Rivero (Vancouver Whitecaps FC) in the box is blocked by Ronald Zubar (New York Red Bulls).
timelineItems.title: BLOCK: Ronald Zubar makes big stop

timelineItems.name: Rituro
timelineItems.text: I mean, that Waston/Kljestan incident... I dunno. Waston's a big guy. Unless Kljestan somehow got him in the vulnerables... #VWFC #NYvVAN

timelineItems.name: Guy L. Gonzalez
timelineItems.text: Disastrous start: missed PK, red card. 1-0 is arguably not so bad. Marsch's tactical skills will be tested now. What's Plan B? #rbny #NYvVAN

timelineItems.name: New York Red Bulls
timelineItems.text: 45: 45 more to play, here we go. 0-1 #NYvVAN

timelineItems.name: Joe Tansey
timelineItems.text: Aaron Ramsey's favorite center back may be Aaron Ramsey's favorite actor now too. #NYvVAN https://t.co/wKHmh5Bq9w

timelineItems.name: New York Red Bulls
timelineItems.text: 45: Anatole Abang checks into the match for Sal Zizzo. 0-1 #NYvVAN

timelineItems.text: 100% agree “@86forever: not that it matters now, however, I think it was a foul by Beita but I think it was outside the box.#NYvVAN #VWFC”

timelineItems.text: Looks like Sacha Kljestan been reading Clint Dempsey's Guide to Effective Conflict Resolution. #NYvVAN

timelineItems.name: Dave Martinez
timelineItems.text: Gutsy start to the half from #RBNY w high press on #VWFC ... While down a man. Stick to what works?

timelineItems.name: Vancouver Whitecaps

timelineItems.text: Tremendous turn by BWP ruined by an offside Abang. Could have been a thing of true beauty. #NYvVAN

timelineItems.name: Russ McKenzie
timelineItems.text: Credit to #RBNY for playing as compact as they are. Short simple passes. Incredible composure for a team playing a man down #NYvVAN
